claim.claim-text:
1. A method of controlling a vehicle, the method comprising:
detecting a lane in which a target vehicle is driving and an object in a vicinity of the lane from an image of surroundings of the target vehicle;
tracking a movement of the object;
comparing the tracked movement of the object to a danger pattern; and
controlling the target vehicle based on a result of comparing the tracked movement of the object to the danger pattern,
wherein the danger pattern is associated with at least one of driving pattern in which a vehicle is driving from side to side in a zigzag path based on a center of line, driving pattern in which a center of a vehicle moves from a left side to a right side of a lane and driving pattern in which a center of a vehicle moves from a right side to a left side of a lane.

20. A non-transitory computer-readable storage medium storing instructions that, when executed by a processor, cause the processor to perform:
detecting a lane in which a target vehicle is driving and an object in a vicinity of the lane from an image of surroundings of the target vehicle;
tracking a movement of the object;
comparing the tracked movement of the object to a danger pattern; and
controlling the target vehicle based on a result of comparing the tracked movement of the object to the danger pattern,
wherein the danger pattern is associated with at least one of driving pattern in which a vehicle is driving from side to side in a zigzag path based on a center of line, driving pattern in which a center of a vehicle moves from a left side to a right side of a lane and driving pattern in which a center of a vehicle moves from a right side to a left side of a lane.
